=== Usage ===
Marks a string by [[ISO 15924]] code of script. Switch between {{tl|cuneiform}}, {{tl|Coptic}}, {{tl|Gaelic}}, {{tl|Hebrew}}, {{tl|Nastaliq}}, {{tl|runic}}, {{tl|Slavonic}}.

The [[Nastaʿlīq script|Nasta'liq script]] is considered a font variant by both Unicode and ISO 15924. Use ur-Arab, ps-Arab or fa-Arab to access {{tl|Nastaliq}}.

unaddressed is the selection of individual [[East Asian calligraphy|Chinese typefaces]] ([[ISO 15924:Hani|Hani]]), should be solved via {{tl|lang}}.

